<p>Verbs do not change their forms to reflect past, present, or future tenses. Instead, aspect markers like the perfective particle <code>le</code> can be appended to show completed actions. Words fluidly shift roles depending on context -- for instance, <code>chi</code> represents the action &quot;to eat&quot; or the noun &quot;food,&quot; while <code>zhidao-de ren</code> acts as &quot;a knowledgeable person&quot;.</p>
